</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Any <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000W/" title="Inverse" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000W/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000W/" type="local">invertible</fr:link> map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001T/" title="n-truncated map" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001T/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001T/" type="local">contractible</fr:link>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>30</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon  \colon  f\circ  f^{-1} = 1_{B}]]></fr:tex> be the counit of the <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000W/" title="Inverse" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000W/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000W/" type="local">inverse</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex>. Given <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b:B]]></fr:tex>, we must show that the fiber of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H/" title="Contractible type" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H/" type="local">contractible</fr:link>; the centre of contraction is given by the pair 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen f^{-1} x, \epsilon  x\right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
, and the required paths can be constructed via the <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001R/" title="path object structure on fibers" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001R/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001R/" type="local">univalence principle for fibers</fr:link> using the unit <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta \colon  f^{-1}\circ  f = 1_{A}]]></fr:tex>, the coherence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\circ \eta \sim \epsilon \circ  f]]></fr:tex>, and the <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001V/" title="Naturality of homotopies" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001V/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001V/" type="local">naturality of homotopies</fr:link>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
